  "packageName": "@cubid/comms",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/comms`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nSigned-in messaging profile helpers for Cubid Passport notification channels and\npreferences.\n\nUse "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/comms`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " when a Passport-authenticated user needs to manage\nCubid-owned notification channels, verification steps, or messaging\npreferences without exposing raw destinations or provider internals to the app.\n\nChoose this package instead of:\n\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/core`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for Passport-user profile management surfaces\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/browser`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for hosted browser flows\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/react`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for React-specific UI composition\n\nUse "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/core`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " later for server-authenticated dapp notification send and\nstatus helpers. Those APIs stay separate from signed-in user channel\nmanagement.\n\n## Install\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\npnpm add @cubid/comms\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Registry availability\n\n- npm-only\n\n## API reference\n\n- Root package matrix: [/Users/botmaster/src/cubid/cubid-sdk-v2/README.md](/Users/botmaster/src/cubid/cubid-sdk-v2/README.md)\n- Machine-readable API reference: [/Users/botmaster/src/cubid/cubid-sdk-v2/docs/reference/api/comms.json](/Users/botmaster/src/cubid/cubid-sdk-v2/docs/reference/api/comms.json)\n\n## Current scope\n\nThis first package slice defines the signed-in Passport-user client boundary for\nfuture flexible messaging helpers.\n\nIt intentionally does not add:\n\n- dapp-authenticated notification send helpers\n- hosted Allow Page grant wrappers\n- raw email addresses, Telegram identifiers, ciphertext, or provider secrets\n\nThose behaviors remain deferred to later roadmap slices."
    }
  ]
}
